      "host": "tribuneindia.com",
      "text": "Tribune News Service\nBathinda, October 22\nThe police today booked former gangster Lakha Sidana in two cases for allegedly defacing signboards. The cases were registered at the Thermal and Nehianwala police stations on the complaints of the PWD (B&R) Department. No arrest has been made so far. Led by Sidana, members of the Malwa Youth Federation, Dal Khalsa and other organisations had blackened English and Hindi messages on signboards under the “Save Punjabi” campaign. Investigating officer Gurmail Singh said Sidana and Hardeep Singh Baba, along with 50-60 unidentified persons, defaced signage on the Bathinda-Goniana road. A case under Sections 3 of the Prevention of Damage to Public Property Act, 1984, and Section 5 of the Punjab Prevention of Defacement of Property Ordinance Act, 1997, was registered at the Thermal police station. In the other case, Sidana. Hardeep and 70-80 unidentified persons damaged public property on the Hariraipur-Goniana Bhokhra road, investigating officer Maghar Singh said. Sidana said he would not seek bail and instead produce himself in the court as he had done nothing unlawful. “I will demand dismissal of the case and continue my fight to save the Punjabi language,” he added.",
