      "title": "Jaypee Infratech: SC asks Jaiprakash Associates to provide fund raising plan to IRP, IBBI, IDBI Bank & AG, Real Estate News, ET RealEstate",
      "country": "IN",
      "crawl_date": "2017-10-24T01:48:00Z",
      "url": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/sc-asks-jaiprakash-associates-to-provide-fund-raising-plan-to-irp-ibbi-idbi-bank-ag/61189490",
      "host": "realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com",
      "text": "Delhi-NCR SC asks Jaiprakash Associates to provide fund raising plan to IRP, IBBI, IDBI Bank & AG Jaiprakash Associates earlier this month had informed the Supreme Court that it wants to sell off the Yamuna Expressway to generate money Sanu Sandilya | ETRealty | October 23, 2017, 21:24 IST NEW DELHI: The Supreme Court on Monday asked Jaiprakash Associates to provide the proposal for raising money to the insolvency resolution professional, the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Board of India, IDBI Bank and the Attorney General.The case has now been listed for hearing on October 25 at 3 pm.Jaiprakash Associates earlier this month had informed the Supreme Court that it wants to sell off the Yamuna Expressway to generate money. It had also told the apex court that it has an offer worth Rs 2,500 crore from a company.\"Jaiprakash Associates wants to sell off the Yamuna Expressway and deposit the money in an escrow account, a proposal which was opposed by us in the court today,\" said advocate Ashwarya Sinha, who represented the first petitioners in the case.The company also sought to give to the court the proposal to hive off the Yumuna Expressway and informing about the proposed buyer, etc, in a sealed cover.The application filed by Jaiprakash Associates and its attempt to give the proposal in a sealed cover were opposed by the Attorney General, who stared that any proposal which affected so many people could not be given in a sealed cover, according to Sinha.The Supreme Court on September 11 had asked Jaiprakash Associates to deposit Rs 2,000 crore by October 27 to pay off the aggrieved home buyers.About 32,000 home buyers were left in the lurch after the Allahabad bench of the National Company Law Tribunal ( NCLT ) on August 9 classified Jaypee Infratech , a subsidiary of Jaiprakash Associates, as insolvent on the petition filed by IDBI Bank under Section 7 of Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code 2016. Jaypee had defaulted on a Rs 526-crore loan by the bank.However, the Supreme Court on September 4 stayed insolvency resolution proceedings against Jaypee Infratech on a plea by home buyers of its projects in Noida. IDBI Bank on September 5 moved the apex court demanding the stay order to be vacated.The apex court on September 11 re-initiated the insolvency resolution proceedings against Jaypee Infratech and gave its management control to the IRP, appointed by the National Company Law Tribunal, with immediate effect.The apex court has also asked the professional to submit an interim plan to SC within 45 days keeping in view the interest of homebuyers. RELATED",
