      "title": "NGT raps authorities over Yamuna project",
      "country": "IN",
      "crawl_date": "2017-10-24T06:32:07Z",
      "url": "http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/ngt-raps-authorities-over-yamuna-project/article19910395.ece",
      "host": "thehindu.com",
      "text": "October 24, 2017 08:11   08:11 IST more-in Delhi Jal Board asked to file detailed reply within 10 days \nThe National Green Tribunal (NGT) on Monday rapped the Delhi Jal Board (DJB) and the Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) government for not complying with its previous orders with regard to the Yamuna cleaning project. Further, the green panel asked both the authorities to show cause regarding the same within 10 days. \nThe Bench headed by NGT chairperson Swatanter Kumar met officials from the State government, Delhi Development Authority (DDA), DJB, Larsen and Toubro and National Mission for Clean Ganga in the NGT premises. \nDefying orders \nMr. Kumar pulled up the authorities for defying the orders that were earlier passed by the tribunal and said that except for shifting blame, the authorities had no other reason to explain their ‘in-action and non-cooperation’ towards the project. \nSewage treatment plants \nThe green panel also rapped the DJB for not setting up the sewage treatment plants that were required. \nReplying to the Bench regarding the same, the counsel appearing for the DJB said that necessary proceedings will be initiated and that the delay was because of certain decision-making processes by the board. \nDDA counsel \nThe counsel appearing for the DDA, on the other hand, said that they had complied with the NGT orders and were also releasing the money that the DJB had asked for. \nPhase-I of the Clean Yamuna Project dealt with lowering the pollution levels in the Najafgarh and Delhi Gate drains, while Phase-II dealt with Shahdara, Barapullah and other drain systems. \nIn the previous order, the green panel had also asked as to why ‘appropriate orders in relation to attachment of their accounts be not passed and the proceedings for non-compliance of the orders of the tribunal be not initiated’. \nIt had said that the pollution in the Yamuna was a serious concern as industrial effluents contaminated it highly. \nThe DJB is now expected to file a detailed reply within 10 days.",
