      "host": "meghalayatimes.info",
      "text": "GHSMC moving ahead with Garoland demand   \nStaff Reporter TURA, Oct 23: Buoyed by their talks with the centre, the Garo Hills State Movement Committee (GHSMC) is set to hold a public rally in the town of Tura in support of their demand for a separate Garoland state on November 15.Announcing the event, the committee’s chairman, Nikman Ch Marak said, “Recently from 1-5 August, we approached the Prime Minister, Narendra Modi at Delhi on the matter and submitted a memorandum on the demand for a separate Garoland state.” \n“We demanded a separate state to include the five districts of Garo Hills. We held fruitful meeting with Minister of State, Kiren Rijiju, Home Minister, Rajnath Singh and Shillong MP, Vincent Pala. A copy of the memorandum was also submitted to the office of the president of India and the office of the PM,” he added.The GHSMC later held a meeting on September 9 under the chairmanship of Nikman at Tura.“We demand a separate state under the Constitution of India framed by Pt. Jawaharlal Nehru, in order to safeguard tribal societies of India like Garos under the Article 3, creation of new state for the distinct language and culture under State Re-Organisation Act, 1956,” stated the release.Incidentally the rally on November 15 at Tura Chandmary playground would be the 21st such rally undertaken by the GHSMC in support for their demand.“We would like to request all, without bias to come forward and support the movement for a separate state. We would also like to request the entire Garo Community of entire North-East Region, the state, the country and the world to give support to make this a global event,” added the GHSMC.The rally is set to start at 11 am on the said date.",
