      "host": "infraline.com",
      "text": "Show Less BPCL arm bags 15-year diesel export deal with Bangladesh Petroleum Corporation \nNumaligarh Refinery Ltd (NRL), the Assam-based subsidiary of state-run Bharat Petroleum Corporation has inked a 15-year agreement with Bangladesh Petroleum Corporation (BPC) for exporting gas oil (off road diesel), becoming the first Indian company to sign a long-term fuel supply deal with Bangladesh. The heads of the two companies signed the deal in the presence of external affairs minister Sushma Swaraj, who concluded her two-day visit to Bangladesh. The deal fits well into the Narendra Modi government's look-east policy and elevates the bilateral engagement with wider energy trade. Bangladesh is already plugged into the Indian grid and imports power.BPC will initially import up to a quarter million tonne per annum (MTPA) of gas oil from",
